I have a story with this song to share. I was bullied at the  school I used to study. Every day was a hell. I had known all those people for almost a decade, and I hated each one. My mother knew how much I hated that place, how much I wanted to change to another School  and  forget those people, so she moved me this year to a new place. Last year were my last moments in that hell, and I remember well that on the last day of school before the holidays, I listened in loop to this song. I was going to tell everyone that  hurted me about how I felt when it was time to leave, but when I heard again the chorus "Never care for what they do," I just left everything behind, I remained in silence and went home alone as always, but this time there were no tears, just relief. How to Receive Your Heavenly Prayer Language
His Inspirational Gifts:
Manifestation and Church Gift of Divers Kinds of
Tongues...1Corinthians 12:4-11
Mark 16:17...Divers kinds of tongues is supernatural utterance by the Holy Spirit in languages never learned by the speaker, not
understood by the mind of the speaker, nor necessarily always understood by the hearer. Speaking with tongues has nothing
whatsoever to do with linguistic ability; it has nothing to do with the mind or the intellect of man. It is a vocal miracle.
Tongues is primarily a devotional gift
Jesus told his disciples, "After the Holy Ghost has come upon you, you shall receive power" (Acts 1:8). The evidence of this baptism is
the gifts of the Spirit, with tongues almost invariably coming
first. There are various kinds of tongues. One type‚Äîthe prayer and worship language‚Äîis for private use and personal edification. It
does not need to be interpreted. In fact, Paul informs us that although he spoke in tongues more often than all the Corinthians,
when he did, his understanding was unfruitful. He describes his use of a prayer language as praying "with the spirit" (1 Corinthians
14:14-15). This prayer and worship language is indispensable for every Spirit-filled Christian.
Public ministry of tongues
Paul teaches that only a few believers will be used in what we would call the public ministry of tongues, because he said in 1
Corinthians 12:30, "do all speak with tongues?" Some take that out of context and say, "Speaking in tongues isn't for everyone. You can
be filled with the Spirit without speaking with tongues." However, we must remember that Paul is talking about the ministry gift of
tongues, because he began by saying, "And God hath set some in thechurch...diversities of tongues" (1 Corinthians 12:28). Then Paul
asked, "Are all apostles?...do all speak with tongues?" The obvious answer is no. But Paul is talking here about public ministry. We
should not be too concerned about our ministering in tongues and interpreting. We should be primarily concerned with maintaining
tongues in the place where they principally belong‚Äîas a devotional gift to assist us in the worship of God.
Why should I speak in tongues? Speaking in tongues is initial evidence of Holy Spirit baptism...Acts 2:1-4; 10:44-48; 19:1-6.
Speaks unto God...1 Corinthians 14:2.
Speaks in mysteries...1 Corinthians 14:2.
For spiritual edification...1 Corinthians 14:4.
Build up yourself...Jude 20.
Pray for the unknown--don't know what or how to pray in any
situation...Romans 8:26-27.
Produces rest in our Souls...Isaiah 28:11-12.
Out of your belly shall flow the river of Life...John 7:37-38.
People often ask me why tongues is a common manifestation of baptism in the Holy Spirit. I tell them that if God is going to rule
us, He must certainly rule our tongues; it is our most unruly member. Just as we grab a bit to control a horse, God takes hold of
our tongue to assert His control of us.
Another reason He gives the gift of tongues first is to enable us to build our faith for the appropriation of other spiritual
gifts...How are we to appropriate these gifts? Martin Luther tells
us, "Faith is the arm that reaches out to take the gift God offers." But our arm of faith is weak and short. So God's first gift is the
only one that edifies the user. With it, we can build up our arm of faith to appropriate other gifts we may need. That's why when
someone with a great need comes to me, I find myself instinctively praying in tongues.
Because tongues, above the other gifts, is a worship gift, it helps us fulfill our primary reason for being: to glorify God and
enjoy Him.
Folks always ask me, "Do I have to speak in tongues to receive the baptism in the Holy Spirit?" I give them evangelist David
Wilkerson's answer: "You don't have to. You get to. It's part of the package."
How do I speak in tongues?
Instead of telling people to ask for the gift of tongues, I urge them, with the words of the apostle Paul, to "stir up the gift of
God which is in you" (2 Timothy 1:6).
1. You make the sound by furnishing the raw material. God helps you with the utterance. He helps you shape the sound of your voice
into words. Acts 2:4 says, "And they were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and began to speak with other tongues, as the Spirit gave
them utterance."
2. Don't speak words your mind understands. As long as you do, your mind will remain in control.
3. Don't listen to yourself. Can you imagine a little child learning to talk? Does he say, "Ma-ma-ma-ma," and then stop with: "I

This song is almost hard to listen to for me.  I remember listening to it on a trip to Colorado.  It was a rainy day so we sat in my dad's van, me a few friends, my little brother and my dad.  He never liked Metallica but was a musician himself and appreciated good music.  I had just gotten this album (on cassette).  We just watched an amazing lightning storm in the best of nature.  It opened my dad to a lot of other music that he didn't normally listen to.  That was twenty six years ago, lost him last year.  Every time I hear this song, that memory comes up.

True story...
My friends and I walked into a music store.  One friend picks up a guitar and starts picking out this song, store man looks at my friend then points to a sign that says, " no playing, " Nothing else matters"... lol
Store man grabs the guitar and says, "it's flat anyway", then tunes it up.  Not long after he tunes the guitar, he pops it onto the stand and before my friend grabs it again, some guy walked in and swooped up the now tuned guitar.  lol...  anyway this stranger then plucks each string and says, "this is way out of any key" - us and music store man look on hahaha.  
The stranger tunes the guitar beautifully and then he started playing, Nothing Else Matters.  He played it beautifully and then started jamming out some Hendrix.  Anyways I really felt bad for my friend, I used to think he was good on the guitar but the stranger was amazing.  In my best effort I turned to my friend and gestured at the stranger saying, "ugh he's a show off, let's go".   Fast forward 25 years, I'm married to the show off stranger and we have 4 grown children.   
Good musicians always score lol

Oh, so you're trying to get into Metallica? Go to Load or ReLoad, those albums are full of Rock subgenres and nice slow songs. And whenever you think you're ready, go to  Ride the Lightning or Kill 'em All, those albums are full of Thrash Metal and Speed Metal. It's a small step into Metallica's best songs. Then when you've been a while in Ride the Lightning or Kill 'em All, go to the Black Album. It should prepare you for what's coming. You should like most songs like Nothing Else Matters, Enter Sandman, The Unforgiven, and Sad but True. Of Wolf and Man and Holier Than Thou are good tracks too. When you have went through the Black Album, you should be ready. Master of Puppets, ...And Justice for All, Death Magnetic, and Hardwired... to Self-Destruct have the fastest, heaviest tracks Metallica has ever done. You can thank me later.

That is the old Little Mountain Studios in Vancouver, BC. I used to go and hang with my friends at that studio when Bruce Fairburn was there. Sadly, now it's gone. But we had such a blast lstening to music there and getting drunk and dancing there. Lots Of bands recorded their music there, Bob Jovi, Loverboy, Aerosmith, AC/DC...the list goes on. It was because my friend knew Bruce and Mike as to why we got to go in there. When the Nothing Else Matters video came out, we instantly recognized the studio.

This song, among many, certainly solidifies, in my view, Lars Ulrich's sobriquet as rock's greatest drummer. Yes, that title usually resides with the late Led Zeppelin drummer¬†John Bonham and, admittedly, Bonham was often tasked with more melodic challenges,¬†but in a studied comparison (and with latter day recording quality a definite plus), Ulrich seems to me to be more of the dominating force within his band, with his talents much more on display. Each was, of course, a powerhouse percussionist, but Ulrich overwhelms without losing sight of the song's goal. Bonham certainly added his signature to Zep's work but wasn't as prevalent as Ulrich, either in the development of the tune nor, sometimes, in the execution whereas Ulrich is ALWAYS there. With this analysis though, please don't misunderstand my motives for this commentary...I fucking LOVE John Bonham and Led Zeppelin. This comparison is like splitting hairs...these are two monster drummers and talents who dwarf all others. I just felt that a thoughtful comparison was warranted, having not seen one previously (although if any reader HAS seen one before, please include a link in your rebuttle and or comment...I'd love to read another opinion.)Lastly, and almost completely off-topic from this comparison, little is ever discussed about drummers who populate soul-funk bands. The mission of drummers of that genre¬†is to typically¬†carry out the heavy groove with their¬†bass player counterparts. For years as a teenager¬†though I was always¬†impressed with the drummer for the Ohio Players, James "Diamond" Williams, especially on¬†one of their Mercury Record breakout songs "Jive Turkey." Even today I still listen to much of their catalogue and if you are a drummer aficionado, you MUST listen and appreciate this talent. This song appeared on the band's¬†1974 album "Skin Tight" and launched the group into super-stardom. Give a listen, you won't be disappointed.

Hi There Metallica Boys. Metallica Has Been A Part Of My Life As A Musician Infact Since The Release Of The Black Album In 1990! Outstanding Album & Put Metallica In The Spot Light For The First Time Commercially On Screen From The Release Of "One" I Guess But Indeed Bought A New Aspect To Their Talents Or You's Guys Talents. In The Way Metallica Finally Was Hitting The Airwaves & Bringing A Pretty Heavy Metal Ballad Such As "Nothing Else Matters" To Peoples Attention. Infact This Is Roughly When I Started As A Musician & Started Learning Metallica Songs Slowly & Did Over The Next Few Years Backtrack Through Metallica History & Learnt Their Albums Before This! It Is Here I Knuckled Down As A Musician Progressing As A Muso Learning Other Bands Such As GNR And A Little Later Bonjovi!!! I Would Say My 3 Favourite Bands Of All Time & Indeed Forms The Influences Which Contribute To My Acheivements In The Music Industry Today. My Band "Saunders Alive" Which Is Yet To Be Recruited & Yet To Start Off Their Journey But Prospective Outlook In Place For The Future!!! I Did Infact Have A Metallica Cover Band Formed In "1994" Which Played Several Gigs Here In Adelaide, Hindley Street, City Clubs & Port Adelaide Also For A Period Of Time Along With Many Partys We Played Also! We Had Our Manager Also Which Was A Devoted You Could Say One Eyed "Metallica" Fan Which Did Infact Bring Me A Pretty Close Relationship With This Gentleman Also As Lead Guitarist/Vocalist. The Band We Called "No Remorse" & We Did Infact Train Hard As We Were All Huge Fans Of "Metallica" & Our Age Group Was From 15-18 As A Three Piece! My Brother "Jason" Was On Drums As He Does Luv You Guys & Also Luvs A Hit At Times & I Found A Guitarist In The Paper Or "Musicians Connection Service" By The Name Of Matt! I Did Infact Talk Matt Later After Several Session To Take Up Bass As We Needed To Make The Band Fullfilling Enough To Get A Move Along!!! We Went Out & Found A Bass At A Local Porn Shop & We Were Away In A New Direction! We Used To Play Day & Night "Metallica" Material After All Moving Into "Bob" The Managers House Which "Bob" Unfortunately Had A Tragic Accident A Little Earlier In Life & Was Paralised From Waist Down! The Band He Was Now Managing Was A Big Lift For Him In Life As Us Fellows Moving In & Everybody Started To See This A Serious Day To Day Lifestyle For The Next Couple Of Years Even. We Had Great Friends Surrounding Us Which Supported The Band In A Numerous Amount Of Ways Also. Which Gave Us Confidents As Musicians To Fullfill Our Desire "To Do It" & Keep At It Day In Day Out!!! Great Friends Indeed! My Brother Took Up Drums Somewhere Around 1990 Also The Year Of The "Black Album" & Matt I Think Was A Long Term Muso As Myself At This Stage! Matt Did Infact End Up With The Nick Name "Cliffy" Named After Your Outragesly Gifted Deceased Member Cliff Burton As He Played Very Gifted & Picked Up Extraudinary Quick Talented Bass Playing Indeed & Did Infact Play With His Fingers & You Could Say Also Got His Nick Name Through Being A Fan Also Of His Rock Or Ours Infact "Cliff Buton". Anyway, Thats A Bit Of A Look At The History Of Us As Musicians & Metallica Fans. Ive Now Been In The Industry For 27 Yrs As A Musician & Have Now Formed My Own Band "Saunders Alive" As My Time As A Muso & Have 3 Bands Including "Metallica" For My Acheivements To Date In This Industry As My Main Influences In Style & Devoting My Life To Music Through The Songs Ive Worked Covering All You's Fantastic Artists Over The Years!!! Im Listening To This Song Tonight As I've Already Expressed On My Other "Rock Icons" Songs & How I Can Relate To Them & Also Not To Forget "Metallica" Has Been One Of The Main Bands I've Focused On Over The Years Of My Playing & As A Fan. Also I Chose This Song Tonight To Listen To As I Have Infact Had Some Downfalls In Life Which Has Been A Set Back But Has Made Me More Desirable To Succeed With What Im Doing & Be Brave & Look At The "Bright Side Of Things" & Keep Perceaviering To Acheive My Goals I Set Out To Do Many Years Ago!!! So I Guess That Explains Tonights "Reminicents" Of Your Beutiful Ballad Sung Beutifully By "James Hetfield" From The Heart & I Would Say At The Peak Of You Guys & His Singing Career Which Just Goes To Say "Nothing Else Matters" When Life Can Let You Down & Not Quite Work Out As Things Were Expected To But Now We Could Say In All Due Coarse...... I Luv Metallica. I Have My Own "Saunders Alive" Youtube & Soundcloud Channels For People To Explore!!! Cheers Guys!

Your Fan & Friend "Mark Saunders" From Saunders Alive!

We are going to talk about the Crown and all the Presidents since the Spanish Transition and we propose that they are responsible for a crime of Genocide that should be punished with a penalty of between 8 and 15 years in prison.

The genocide was incorporated into the penal code of Spain in 1971 (four years before Franco's death). The Organic Law of the Judiciary of 1985 (Organic Law of the Judiciary, Organic Law 6/1985) grants Spanish courts jurisdiction over acts committed outside Spain where the conduct would violate Spanish law if committed in Spain or violates the obligations derived from international treaties. The law gives Spanish courts jurisdiction over other crimes that international treaties require Spain to prosecute, including genocide and terrorism, and in which treaties require that Spain prosecute such crimes.

The Association of Relatives of Victims of the Genocide of Paracuellos del Jarama presented in 1998, under the protection of the process undertaken in Spain against the former Chilean dictator Augusto Pinochet, a complaint before the National Court against Santiago Carrillo, the PCE, the PSOE, the Community of Madrid and the Spanish State for crimes of genocide, torture and terrorism. The numbers of low natality reach parameters of 7 million descent analogous to the extermination during the Nazi period.

DEMOCRACY IS A DESIRABLE SYSTEM IN THEORY AND INEFFICIENT IN PRACTICE; OR DO YOU ALSO HAVE DEFICIENT AND UNDESIRABLE THEORY?

Unmasking Democracy is difficult in a context in which the media proclaim it to the four winds as the summum of humanity. But his rhetoric is based on ideas presented in a way that can be considered despicable and on which we will try to offer light. Let's start by establishing if it is an ideology.

Let's see:

1. The DLE defines the term ideology and in its first meaning says; A set of fundamental ideas that characterizes the thinking of a person, community or epoch, of a cultural, religious or political movement, etc.

Indeed, within what Gustavo Bueno would call an ideological nebula, we find that there are several central ideas that support the democratic argument; the Right to Vote, the Right to Choose, Freedom, Equality, the Majority ... They are axioms within the democratic ideology.

Gustavo Bueno establishes a substantial difference between the concepts of Ideology and Philosophy and says; whereas, in philosophy, some propositions, statements or premises are presented on which an abstract argument is constructed, that is, one related to ideas or metaphysical, which will serve to implement a dialectic so that Through it we can reach an understanding with our interlocutor, who in turn will present his own criteria. In ideology, these propositions are not debatable but are presented as axioms, that is, an argument is started on pre-established ideas that do not admit discussion.

In this sense, Gustavo Bueno points out that unlike the philosophy that pursues an understanding of universal type, in ideology the body of ideas on which the argument is constructed is presented by opposition to a thought that is different, not accepting the discussion that concerns the axioms that are given for sure in the democratic ideology in this case. These two questions can be very useful when identifying the ideological condition presented by the democratic argument in which several of its central ideas are given as indisputable as for example: the will must be that of the majority, the right to vote it represents freedom, nothing obscure is seen in the fact of choosing people, whatever it may be, etc.

Is it possible to buy a quarter of a kilo of voting rights, freedom, equality, majority? No. These are intangible, immaterial or metaphysical issues, that is, ideas; I will mention this quotation from Voltaire in case it can offer clarity about what metaphysics is: "When, from the speaker and the speaker, neither of them understands what it means, then we can say that it is metaphysical". Voltaire

In order to continue with our observation that aims to clarify whether democracy is an ideology, the post-structuralist prominent Jean-Francois Lyotard in the context of postmodernity points out the metanarratives that; ¬´... any attempt to make an ideological system politically carries within itself the germ of totalitarianism ...¬ª and points out: ..., that is, that the determination of plurality from a single point of view that is imposed by all possible means it has a totalitarian character ¬ª.

Let's see also this summary about the work of Gustavo Bueno, Democracy as ideology: "The article delves into the question of democracy understood as a system of ideologies that involve the functioning of the really existing democratic political systems. Its very definition as "government of all" begins being ideological inasmuch as it takes for granted the superior legitimacy of a majority to represent the totality. But in addition to being weak the arguments in which this supposition is supported, the own determination of the majorities rests in arbitrary arithmetical criteria. After presenting a classification of democratic ideologies, he warns of the dangerous tendency of the idea of ‚Äã‚Äãdemocracy to become a Hegelian metaphysics that, in the manner of Self-consciousness, aims to become a human destiny and the culmination of history ¬ª.

For his part, Benjamin Frankin expresses it very clearly: Democracy is two wolves and a lamb voting to decide what is going to have dinner; while freedom is the lamb, well armed, challenging the vote.

In effect, with respect to what I will refer to as democratic ideology, we find as a central argument the superiority and protection determined by law of those who are in majority even when it is a question of arithmetic and not real.

Now, if nature endows any individual with greater virtues of any kind than another because it makes us different, it is not vain to think that those who stand out are less, that is, they are in a minority. Well it will be therefore that those who are better are also less and the others more. This is not a problem since the fact that they are more numerous already per se is an advantage over minority groups. So, why should an added artificial advantage be established for those who already have the numerical superiority, determining that what the majority says will be done? Crass error of precept that shows the deceitfulness of this ideology called democracy.

At this point, we can begin the study of the main ideas on which this ideology is based such as: The Right to Vote, The Will of the Majority, Freedom, Equality.

In a brief analysis on the Right to Vote, we find in a first observation the chronological order according to which the different countries of Europe are granting this proclaimed right to its citizens, being that the use of this ideology coincides as a form of government in rigorous order, with countries that since ancient times have proven to be more xenophobic and racist, and so we have to be: between 1906 and 1928; Finland, Norway, Denmark, Iceland, Russia, Austria, Czech Republic, Slovakia, Estonia, Hungary, Germany, Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Poland, Sweden, Ireland, Lithuania, Romania, United Kingdom ...

Through the Vow the human being assumes the right to exclude other human beings. Yes, I say exclude because if we look at the meaning of the word choose we find that choosing means choosing. Choose which comes from the Latin and consists of two concepts ex and colligere, that is, leave out and take, therefore it does not matter to say right to vote, which right of exclusion since both actions are exercised simultaneously being inseparable. I suggest that it is good for a person to choose the car that he likes or what to wear but choosing people is a reification of the human being that even if he voluntarily submits to being elected, even when he does so to be chosen as the ruler. What must draw attention is that the fact that being able to choose human beings as a system of government supposes per se the violation of humanity itself, which denigrates itself by submitting to this improper vexation, when the highest and noble aspiration of man and the one that guarantees its harmonious coexistence is the trust and not the arithmetic ...

DEMOCRACY IS GENOCIDE

Certainly, with the so-called Spanish democracy, the population of the country decreases markedly. The figures are truly striking: Between 1940 and 1975, that is to say in a period of 35 years, there was an increase in the Spanish population of some 10 million inhabitants; being the number of immigrants almost non-existent or negligible. The population went from 26,014,278 inhabitants in 1940 to 36,012,682 in 1975.

However, in a period of 39 years, between 1975 and 2014, the increase in population has been the same, some 10 million inhabitants, with the particularity that of these 5 million are immigrants, not to mention the Spanish nationalized, to the second generation of immigrants born with the condition of Spaniards and to the six million unemployed.

In case the above data were not very clear, the INE in its press release of November 19, 2012, makes a projection of the population in 2012 and announces the following conclusions:

-The current demographic trends would lead Spain to lose a tenth of its population in 40 years.
-By 2018 there would be more deaths than births.
-37% of the population would be over 64 years old in 2052.

The population of Spain would be estimated at 41.6 million, 10% less than at present. It would be a second reduction of 10% of the population added to the one suffered during the last 39 years.

While the world population increases to reach today the 7,455,568,571 inhabitants. The Spanish population decreases at a rate of 10% every 40 years, with a 10% reduction corresponding to the last 39 years replaced by a foreign population. Knowing these alarming data, we are ready to consider a brief historical review of the concept of genocide coined by Raphael Lemkin.

After fleeing the national-socialist persecution and finding asylum in the US, it was the Jewish-Polish jurist Raphael Lemkin who in 1939 first coined the term.

From the Greek noun genos (race, people) and the Latin suffix cide (de cadere, matar) Lemkin composed the word genocide.

Lemkin thus defined genocide in his book The Power of the Axis in Occupied Europe published in 1944: The implementation of coordinated actions that tend to the destruction of the decisive elements of the life of national groups, with the aim of their annihilation . When a nation is destroyed, it is not the burden of a ship that is destroyed, but a substantial part of humanity, with a spiritual inheritance that all humanity shares.

The term was recognized by UN Resolution 96 of 1946 however, the pressure of the Soviet Union made the definition of genocide fall the reference to political and other groups that appeared in the UN Resolution 96, thus safeguarding Stalinist foreign policy during the war and the postwar period. Article II of the convention considered genocide, therefore, to any act committed with the intention of destroying, in whole or in part, a national, ethnic, racial or religious group but not a political or other group, as stated in the resolution of 1946

But, why, as the world population increases, that of Spain decreases; 10% in the last 39 years and with the foresight to go back another 10% in the next 40 years? we speak in total of a figure of 10 million inhabitants. For two consecutive times 10% of the population and that is why I want to refer here to a fact that is included in The True Soviet History; and that is: at first when communism came to power and it does not matter where, either; Russia, Poland, Cuba, Nicaragua, China ..., at first they annihilated 10% of the population, it is a concrete fact. it was not only to kill their enemies, they were not enemies, it was about reorganizing the structure of society, social engineering, the main intellectuals, the best workers, the best engineers, they would kill them all and then try to restructure the new society.

It is worth asking: is it, the Spanish democracy, a legalized genocide? In our days, everyone praises democracy, they often say that it is the best form of government. But what would happen if everything were really a hoax? What if it were directly false that democracy is the best known system of government? Moreover, what if the truth were that democracy really is the worst model of government designed by man? And if in reality democracy only consists in a true genocide, legalized and agreed by a majority that in the end turns out to be a minority with respect to the whole population?

There is a coincident phenomenon between democracy in Spain and communism. But, how can it be, if in Spain there is the freedom to create a political party through which to participate in public life? Could it be that democracy is far from being as good as it is painted? It occurs in both cases: democracy and communism, a theoretical argument of a scientific nature that presents both ideas as virtuous without realizing that the implementation of them leads to genocidal disasters such as the one we propose are consequences, in the case of democracy, the destructive germ that accompanies it since its birth: consensus.

We are presented in this framework to the consensus as the essence of the benefits of democracy, however, rather it should be considered as the corrupting virus that is gradually destroying this model of government since its implementation. In a democracy, the key question about consensus is: each and every one of the people with the right to passive vote are voting in conscience what is best for the population as a whole, or are voting the best for their particular interests with independence of the luck that the group of citizens can follow under this form of government? The natural response to this approach is that if all men were angels from heaven, democracy would be the best of government systems, the misfortune is that man inhabits the Earth.

My Interpretation:
I read through some of the comments before writing my own opinion of the song's meaningful nature. Some of them were useless and a whole lot'a babble, others were religiously based, which made me want to gague and roll on the floor, and occasionally some good points were mentioned. My interpretation of the song will probably have the same reactions to the ones I'd seen above or worse of ones. So, here I go, I'll try and summerize as best I can!

Nothing Else Matters-Metallica

When I'd first heard this song I was stumped, I didn't know what they were talking about, how could such a melody have lyrics of such dark nature, well, this is how I percieve it after replaying it to the point of having 567 plays on my Itunes:

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


So close, no matter how far
Couldn't be much more from the heart
Forever trusting who we are
And nothing else matters

Comment: The narrator speaks of a first love, or maybe even a true love after searching many years for him/her (perhaps also a signifacant other). In love we need to trust, and even more so in ourselves. The narrator says that in love trust and being true to your heart is all that matters.

Never opened myself this way
Life is ours, we live it our way
All these words I don't just say
And nothing else matters

Comment: The narrator is opening himself to him/her like a book, telling secrets and sharing things he/she'd of never imagined sharing. He/she is having a spur of reality, rebellion even, deciding that their life is their own and that he/she is determined to live it how they want no matter what people say. Being true to you is all that matters.

Trust I seek and I find in you
Every day for us something new
Open mind for a different view
And nothing else matters

Comment: The narrator now is finding a sense of belonging and trust in their significant other, learning new things and keeping an open mind towards what's happening. Being open and willing to change is all that matters.

Never cared for what they do
Never cared for what they know
But I know

Comment: The narrator is accusing people of not caring enough for their actions and shaming them for not using their knoweledge. He says he knows, something of the reality. Perhaps a break in the trust? 

Never opened myself this way
Life is ours, we live it our way
All these words I don't just say

Trust I seek and I find in you
Every day for us, something new
Open mind for a different view
And nothing else matters

Comment: The narrator repeats himself, obviosuly destressed from some event, telling you that he/she needs to stay true to themselves and rebuild a trust. Again, he/she says that trust and staying true is all that matters.

Never cared for what they say
Never cared for games they play
Never cared for what they do
Never cared for what they know
And I know

Comment: Now we know there has been a break somewhere between then and now. The narrator tells us that they don't care about their actions, that they're playing games and know it. He/she might appear oblivious to what's going on, but he/she makes it clear that they KNOW what's happening, that they have and still do.

So close, no matter how far
Couldn't be much more from the heart
Forever trusting who we are
No, nothing else matters

Comment: The song ends with a specific cluster of lyrics, saying that you need to trust in you and not others. He/she says that no matter how far you are, or how close you are to love or something more than what you have, always stay close and true to you, that's all that matters.

Not that I have anything against the music being produced nowadays, in fact contrary to this sentiment that many rock fans have that music these days is "shitty", I still do enjoy some of the music and artists of today as well. However I feel what separates classic old rock music from today's relatively pop music is that it takes a lot more talent, effort, and coordination to make a good rock song than a pop song. Most artists from today only sing and a lot of music production is done for them. Even on stage all they are doing is just singing. Bands like Metallica perform live in front of an audience, creating music right in front of them. Musicians back then were a lot more innovative than musicians now. I do not dislike current music, I just feel that music in the older generation was a lot more pure and that adds a whole new level to it which current musicians can't replicate.

Lead singer and rhythm guitarist James Hetfield wrote the song (credited to Hetfield/Ulrich[citation needed]) in 1990 while he was on the phone with his then girlfriend. Since he held the phone with one hand, he plucked the four open strings of a standard E-minor chord with the other, which eventually made up the first two bars of the song. The lyrics, which talk about being "so close, no matter how far", were also dedicated to his girlfriend, indicating the bond they shared even when Hetfield was on tour. Initially, the song was not meant to be released, as Hetfield had written it for himself, but after drummer Lars Ulrich heard it, it was considered for the album.[1]
